From 3bd70951e694836c07bbbc64cfc2d30694fa162e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 23:15:43 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] encode-session-ffmpeg: Add FFmpeg/rkmpp H.264 encode backend

Add a narrow FFmpeg encode-session backend as a sibling of the VA-API
path. It is H.264-only, whitelists the h264_rkmpp encoder, and requires
zero-copy DRM PRIME / NV12 surfaces, failing closed when low-latency
zero-copy import/export is unavailable so VA-API stays the preferred
path for proper VA-API drivers.

Surfaces are allocated with GBM on the DRM render node (NV12, linear)
and dual-imported into Vulkan and MPP, with a prebuilt
AVDRMFrameDescriptor per surface for zero-copy submission. The encoder
is configured for low latency with fixed QP, and a smoke encode at
startup validates the zero-copy path before the backend is offered.

The backend is wired in behind a new 'ffmpeg' meson feature (auto),
which resolves to the RDP backend plus libavcodec/libavutil/gbm. The
h264_rkmpp encoder itself is resolved at runtime, so only those
libraries are needed at build time.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01EN9JjFVPvgho9JggxZbM7Y
